  "texts": [
    "Originally, image captioning relied heavily on machine translation evaluation techniques such as BLEU [110], ROUGE [111], and METEOR [112] as no image captioning specific metric existed.",
    "However, this changed with the introduction of both CIDEr [113] and SPICE [86].",
    "The performance metrics are detailed in Table 2.The first architecture to use a GNN to improve image captioning was by Yao et al. [39].",
    "In their work, they propose the use of a GCN to improve the feature embeddings of objects in an image.",
    "They first start by applying a Faster RCNN object detector [78] to the image in order to extract feature vectors representing objects."
  ],
